# Goal Description

The objective is to significantly enhance the visual fidelity, styling, and animations of both website versions: the modern "Bites & Sips" and the ancient "Anubis' Table". We will add premium micro-interactions, richer hover states, and more complex CSS animations to elevate the user experience.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **User Review Required**
> Please review the proposed style enhancements below. Let me know if you want any specific color tweaks, entirely new animations, or if you approve the plan as-is.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Bites & Sips (Modern Version)

We will enhance the modern, clean aesthetic with smooth, dynamic interactions.

#### [MODIFY] `bites-and-sips/css/style.css`
- Add a zoom-in hover effect on the menu card images (`transform: scale(1.05)`).
- Enhance the card hover states with a multi-layered soft drop shadow to make them "pop" off the page.
- Smooth out the background color transitions between dark and light modes.
- Update the hamburger menu so the lines seamlessly animate into an "X" when opened.

#### [MODIFY] `bites-and-sips/css/animations.css`
- Upgrade the scroll-reveal animation to have a slight 3D perspective tilt (`rotateX`) as cards slide into view.
- Enhance the card-flip animation in the game section to include a bouncing physics effect at the end of the flip.

---

### Anubis' Table (Ancient Version)

We will lean heavily into the mythical, glowing, and ancient tomb aesthetic.

#### [MODIFY] `anubis-table/css/style.css`
- Enhance the "stone tablet" menu cards by adding an inset shadow to give them a 3D carved depth.
- Add a slow zoom effect to the menu card images on hover, combined with a golden sepia filter that clears when hovered.
- Give the main buttons a continuous slow pulsing glow effect (`box-shadow`) to mimic torchlight.
- Improve the Sarcophagus hamburger menu animation.

#### [MODIFY] `anubis-table/css/animations.css`
- Upgrade the floating hieroglyphs background to fade in and out asynchronously, creating a more mystical, unpredictable atmosphere.
- Enhance the scroll-reveal `unrollScroll` animation for the Anubis game card to feel heavier and more dramatic (like a thick stone slab dropping).

#### [MODIFY] `anubis-table/css/intro.css`
- Polish the sand particle animation in the intro to drift diagonally and vary in size and speed more distinctly.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Load both sites locally in the browser.
- Verify the hover states on menu cards trigger smooth zooms.
- Test the game flips in both versions to ensure the new physics/weight animations apply.
- Ensure the floating hieroglyphs in the Anubis version animate asynchronously without causing performance lag.
